\section{Transportation transitions}
\label{sec:transport_transitions}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

To improve the sustainability of the modern transportation system,
two broad options exist: 
improving efficiency and 
transitioning to sustainable energy sources.


%++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
\subsection{Fuel economy}
\label{sec:transportation_fuel_economy}
%++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Vehicle fuel economy (an example of an efficacy, not an efficiency)
is usually quantified in distance traveled per volume
of fuel consumed\index{efficiency!fuel}\index{efficiency!vehicle}.
The U.S.\ fleet-average fuel economy of cars and trucks has varied 
significantly over the past few decades.
(See Figure~\ref{fig:US_mpg}.)


<<US_mpg, fig.cap="U.S.\\ car, truck, and fleet fuel economy. \\emph{Sources}: \\citet{Hicks:2014tn} and \\citet{NHTSA2019tc}.">>=
